---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SectionLabel from '../components/SectionLabel.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About | Kate Pinney Interiors"
  description="Meet Kate Pinney — Denver interior designer creating warm, livable homes designed around the way you actually live."
>
  <!-- Page hero: short, text-only, centered -->
  <section class="min-h-[40vh] flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-center px-6 py-16 border-b border-divider">
    <h1 class="font-display font-light text-[2.25rem] md:text-[4.5rem] leading-[1.1]">About</h1>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 1: Bio — 2-column -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-20 items-start">
        <!-- Placeholder: large headshot of Kate Pinney (replace with real photo at public/images/kate-headshot.jpg) -->
        <img
          src="https://picsum.photos/seed/kpi-about/600/750"
          alt="Kate Pinney — Denver Interior Designer"
          class="w-full object-cover aspect-[4/5] md:sticky md:top-20"
          loading="eager"
        />
        <div class="pt-4">
          <SectionLabel label="Kate Pinney" />
          <h2 class="font-display font-light text-[1.75rem] md:text-[3rem] leading-[1.15] mb-8">
            Designing Homes That Tell Your Story
          </h2>

          <p class="font-body font-light text-base leading-[1.7] text-text mb-5">
            Kate Pinney grew up surrounded by beautifully made things — her mother's eye
            for arrangement and her father's appreciation for craftsmanship left a quiet
            impression that eventually became a career. After studying interior architecture
            in Denver and working alongside some of Colorado's most respected design firms,
            Kate launched Kate Pinney Interiors to bring a more personal, client-centered
            approach to residential design.
          </p>

          <p class="font-body font-light text-base leading-[1.7] text-text mb-5">
            Her philosophy is simple: a beautiful home should first be a livable one.
            That means listening carefully before drawing a single line — understanding
            how you move through your mornings, what you reach for instinctively, where
            the light falls in the afternoon. Design decisions follow from those truths,
            not from trend books.
          </p>

          <p class="font-body font-light text-base leading-[1.7] text-text mb-5">
            Kate works primarily with Denver-area families on full-home redesigns and
            curated room transformations. Every project is a true collaboration: she
            brings the expertise, her clients bring the stories, and together they build
            spaces that feel genuinely and unmistakably theirs.
          </p>

          <p class="font-body font-light text-base leading-[1.7] text-text">
            When she's not on-site or deep in a floor plan, you'll find Kate hiking
            the foothills, scouring vintage markets for one-of-a-kind finds, or cooking
            elaborate Sunday dinners with her family.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Process steps — 3-column -->
  <section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-surface border-t border-divider">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="text-center mb-14">
        <SectionLabel label="The Process" center />
        <h2 class="font-display font-light text-[1.75rem] md:text-[2.5rem] leading-[1.15]">
          How We Work Together
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-0 md:gap-16 divide-y md:divide-y-0 divide-divider">

        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="py-8 md:py-0">
          <span class="eyebrow text-accent-dark block mb-3">Step 01</span>
          <h3 class="font-body font-medium text-base tracking-wide uppercase mb-3">Discovery</h3>
          <p class="font-body font-light text-base leading-[1.7] text-muted">
            We begin with a deep-dive conversation about how you live, what you love,
            and what you're ready to leave behind. This listening phase shapes everything
            that follows.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="py-8 md:py-0">
          <span class="eyebrow text-accent-dark block mb-3">Step 02</span>
          <h3 class="font-body font-medium text-base tracking-wide uppercase mb-3">Design</h3>
          <p class="font-body font-light text-base leading-[1.7] text-muted">
            Kate develops a cohesive concept — floor plans, material palettes, furniture
            selections, and lighting plans — presented in a clear, visual format that
            makes collaboration easy and decisions confident.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="py-8 md:py-0">
          <span class="eyebrow text-accent-dark block mb-3">Step 03</span>
          <h3 class="font-body font-medium text-base tracking-wide uppercase mb-3">Installation</h3>
          <p class="font-body font-light text-base leading-[1.7] text-muted">
            On installation day, Kate and her team handle every detail — from furniture
            placement to the final flourish of fresh flowers — so you can walk in to a
            home that's completely, beautifully finished.
          </p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: CTA -->
  <section class="py-24 text-center border-t border-divider">
    <div class="max-w-xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="font-display italic font-light text-[2rem] md:text-[2.5rem] leading-[1.15] mb-8">
        Ready to Start Your Project?
      </h2>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn-outline-dark">Get in Touch</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
